<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 10:01AM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of heavy snow showers will affect Portage...
Trumbull...Mahoning and Stark Counties Until 1130 AM EST....
At 957 AM EST, radar indicated a broad area of snow showers
extending from near Kent to near Lordstown to Canton and Youngstown,
moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to around 1/4 mile...
Up to 1 inch of quick snow accumulation...
Snow may mix with sleet at times...
Roads will become snow covered and slick...
Locations impacted include...
Canton, Youngstown, Warren, Salem, Ravenna, Columbiana, Boardman,
Kent, Alliance, Niles, Tallmadge, North Canton, Streetsboro,
Louisville, Campbell, Hubbard, Canfield, Cortland, Newton Falls and
Sebring.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
